PROS Revenue Management Announces New Board Member

January 3, 2001 - Houston - PROS Revenue Management, the world's leader in revenue management science and the pioneer and dominant provider of revenue management to the airline and energy industries, today announced the addition of Donald R. Sinclair to the PROS Advisory Board.

Mr. Sinclair currently provides strategic consulting services to the energy industry. He has been involved in the energy industry since deregulation began in the early 1980s. He served as President of Duke Energy Trading and Marketing LLC, from April 1997 to September 1998

Prior to joining Duke, Sinclair served as senior vice president of Tenneco Energy and president of Tenneco Energy Resources. As one of the original principals and officers in Dynegy, he served eight years in various officer positions, including senior vice president and chief risk officer, where he was in charge of all risk management activities and commercial operations.

The mission of the PROS Advisory Board is to assist PROS in achieving its strategic objectives and bringing the highest value revenue management products to its clients.

"The PROS Advisory Board consists of industry leaders who share our vision of maximizing the revenue and profit of each client using PROS' revenue management science, software solutions and best-practices consulting expertise," says Bert Winemiller, President and CEO of PROS.

Other members of the Advisory Board consist of:

?	Peter P. Belobaba, Principal Research Scientist in the International Center for Air Transportation at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) and Visiting Professor of Aviation at Concordia University in Montreal; also a leading academic expert on airline revenue management.
?	John R. Birge, Dean of the McCormick School of Engineering and Applied Science at Northwestern University and President of the Institute for Operations Research and the Management Science (INFORMS).
?	Bob Booth, Chairman of AvGroup, a company that advises on aviation related matters in the Latin American and Caribbean markets; also former CEO of Challenge Air International and senior executive with Air Florida, Northeastern and Braniff.
?	E. Russell Braziel, Chairman and Director of Altra Energy Technologies, Inc., the world's leading energy e-commerce exchange and transaction management software company; also formerly with Williams Company and Texaco Gas Marketing.
?	Marc Cavaliere, Vice President and Senior Partner of Aviation Management Services (AvMan), the premier aviation consultancy specializing in the Caribbean, Central America and South America. AvMan is a member of AvGroup.
?	Christopher E. Clouser, Chief Executive Officer & Member of the Executive Board of the Minnesota Twins Major League Baseball Club and former President & CEO of PreviewTravel.com.
?	Robert Frey, President of Robert Frey Media Consultants, a broadcast industry company specializing in sales productivity, revenue maximization, goal alignment of profit and sales and strategic selling; also former General Sales Manager at Meredith Corporation.
?	Richard A. Hosley, Software Technology Consultant and former President of BMC Software.
?	Philip A. Jones, President of PJ Communications Company; formerly senior executive at the Meredith Corporation, and is immediate past Chairman of the National Association of Broadcasters (NAB). He is also Chairman of Broadcast Music Inc. (BMI)
?	Joseph McCall, founder and Managing Partner of Technology Ventures LLC, an investment company, founder of McCall Consulting Group, founder of Clarus Corporation (CLRS) and formerly with Andersen Consulting.
?	Wayne C. New, President of New Consulting Services, a business consulting firm in healthcare management and operations, and former COO of The Children's Hospital in Denver and Driscoll Children's Hospital.
?	Carl J. Schramm, President of Greenspring Advisors, Inc., a healthcare, risk management and information sciences business development and consulting firm; also former Executive Vice President of Fortis, Inc. and former President of the Health Insurance Association of America.
?	Steve Swope, President of The Rubicon Group, Inc. Formerly with Delta Air Lines and Aeronomics Incorporated (now Talus Solutions); he is recognized as a leading authority on revenue management in several industries including rental car, airline, hotel, broadcasting, energy utilities and telecommunications.
?	Garrett J. van Ryzin, Associate Professor, Columbia Graduate School of Business, and Consultant to several major corporations, including AT&T, GE Capital, Northwest Airlines and Priceline.com.



PROS Revenue Management (www.prosRM.com) is the world's leader in revenue management science and the pioneer and dominant provider of yield management (RM) to the airline industry. PROS provides system solutions to the airline, cargo, rail, energy, healthcare and broadcast industries, and has delivered over 180 systems to more than 82 clients in 25 countries.

The PROS mission is to maximize the revenue of each client using PROS' world-leading revenue management science, systems solutions and best practices business consulting. PROS clients report annual incremental revenue increases of 2-8% as a result of revenue management. PROS solutions forecast demand, optimize inventory and provide dynamic pricing to maximize revenue.

Founded in 1985 in Houston, PROS Revenue Management has a five-year compounded revenue growth of 40%, in large part due to the intellectual capital of its staff. Over fifty percent of PROS employees have advanced degrees (56 Masters and 23 PhDs) and the staff speaks a cumulative total of 26 languages. The company is profitable with 1999 revenue exceeding $21 million. PROS' strong balance sheet is evidence of the company's continued success. For more information on PROS Revenue Management, please visit www.prosRM.com or call 713-335-5813.

